02/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government hopes to close four more negotiation chapters -- Free Movement of Services, Agriculture, Energy, and Budget Policies -- in talks with the EU, according to the country's chief negotiator with the Union, Vasile Puscas. 
The pace of accession talks was discussed at a special meeting Tuesday (1 June) called by Prime Minister Adrian Nastase.
In other news Tuesday, Minister Delegate for Public Administration Gabriel Oprea said that local authorities are ready for Sunday's local elections. 
He says the campaigns have been conducted in a "civilised" manner and in accordance with the law. 
(Romanian government Web site - 01/06/04)
